#. type: Title -
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fixes since v2.4"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:13
msgid ""
"The usual \"git diff\" when seeing a file turning into a directory showed a "
"patchset to remove the file and create all files in the directory, but \"git "
"diff --no-index\" simply refused to work.  Also, when asked to compare a "
"file and a directory, imitate POSIX \"diff\" and compare the file with the "
"file with the same name in the directory, instead of refusing to run."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:17
msgid ""
"The default $HOME/.gitconfig file created upon \"git config --global\" that "
"edits it had incorrectly spelled user.name and user.email entries in it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:20
msgid ""
"\"git commit --date=now\" or anything that relies on approxidate lost the "
"daylight-saving-time offset."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:23
msgid ""
"\"git cat-file bl $blob\" failed to barf even though there is no object type "
"that is \"bl\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:28
msgid ""
"Teach the codepaths that read .gitignore and .gitattributes files that these "
"files encoded in UTF-8 may have UTF-8 BOM marker at the beginning; this "
"makes it in line with what we do for configuration files already."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:32
msgid ""
"Access to objects in repositories that borrow from another one on a slow NFS "
"server unnecessarily got more expensive due to recent code becoming more "
"cautious in a naive way not to lose objects to pruning."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:38
msgid ""
"We avoid setting core.worktree when the repository location is the \".git\" "
"directory directly at the top level of the working tree, but the code "
"misdetected the case in which the working tree is at the root level of the "
"filesystem (which arguably is a silly thing to do, but still valid)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../Documentation/RelNotes/2.4.1.txt:40
msgid "Also contains typofixes, documentation updates and trivial code clean-ups."
msgstr ""
